  line
  line `2. Dadra and Nagar Haveli`
  line
  line `3. Himachal Pradesh`
  line
  line `4. Laccadive, Minicoy and Amindivi Islands.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (6756)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Definitions and interpretation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6756&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "Aadhaar number" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (a) of section 2 of`
  line `the Aadhaar (Targeted Delivery of Financial and Other Subsidies, Benefits and Services) Act, 2016`
  line `(18 of 2016);`
  line
  line `(aa) "adoption" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (2) of section 2 of the`
  line `Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, 2015 (2 of 2016);]`
  line
  line `^2[(ab)] "birth" means live-birth or still-birth;`
  line
  line `^1[(b) "database" means the organised collection of data, generally stored and accessed in`
  line `electronic form from a computer network;]`
  line
  line `^3[(ba)] "death" means the permanent disappearance of all evidence of life at any time after`
  line `live-birth has taken place;`
  line
  line `(c) "foetal death" means absence of all evidence of life prior to the complete expulsion or`
  line `extraction from its mother of a product of conception irrespective of the duration of pregnancy;`
  line
  line `(d) "live-birth" means the complete expulsion or extraction from its mother of a product of`
  line `conception, irrespective of the duration of pregnancy, which, after such expulsion or extraction,`
  line `breathes or show any other evidence of life, and each product of such birth is considered live-born;`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the Administrator thereof;`
  line
  line `(g) "still-birth" means foetal death where a product of conception has attained at least the`
  line `prescribed period of gestation.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in this Act to any law which is not in force in any area shall, in relation to that area,`
  line `be construed as a reference to the corresponding law, if any, in force in that area.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2023, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (a) re-numbered as clause (ab) by s. 3, ibid.(w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (b) re-numbered as clause (ba) by s. 3, ibid.(w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (6757)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Registrar General of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6757&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[Registrar General of India.]--(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint a person to be known as the ^1[Registrar General of India], India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may also appoint such other officers with such designations as it thinks`
  line `fit for the purpose of discharging under the superintendence and direction of the ^2[Registrar General of`
  line `India], such functions of the ^2[Registrar General of India] under this Act as he may, from time to time,`
  line `authorise them to discharge.`
  line
  line `(3) The ^2[Registrar General of India] may issue general directions regarding registration of births and`
  line `deaths in the territories to which this Act extends, and shall take steps to co-ordinate and unify the`
  line `activities of Chief Registrars in the matter of registration of births and deaths ^3[and the database of`
  line `registered births and deaths and submit] to the Central Government an annual report on the working of`
  line `this Act in the said territories.`
  line
  line `^4[(4) The Registrar General of India shall maintain the database of registered births and deaths at the`
  line `National level and it shall be obligatory upon the Chief Registrars and the Registrars to share the data of`
  line `registered births and deaths to such database.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 17 and with the prior approval of the Central`
  line `Government, the database of registered births and deaths maintained under sub-section (4) may, on request, be made available to the authorities dealing with the preparation or maintenance of database`
  line `relating to--`
  line
  line `(a) population register;`
  line
  line `(b) electoral rolls;`
  line
  line `(c) Aadhaar number;`
  line
  line `(d) ration card;`
  line
  line `(e) passport;`
  line
  line `(f) driving licence;`
  line
  line `(g) property registration; and`
  line
  line `(h) such other databases at the National level as may be notified,`
  line
  line `and the authority shall inform the action taken, within such period as may be notified from time to time,`
  line `to the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the preparation or maintenance of database relating to electoral rolls in`
  line `clause (b) shall be without prejudice to the provisions of the Representation of the People Act, 1950`
  line `(43 of 1950).]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "Registrar-General, India" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid, for "Registrar-General" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid, for "and submit" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 4 , ibid (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (6758)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Chief Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6758&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint`
  line `a Chief Registrar for the State.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may also appoint such other officers with such designations as it thinks fit`
  line `for the purpose of discharging, under the superintendence and direction of the Chief Registrar, such of his`
  line `functions as he may, from time to time, authorise them to discharge.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Registrar shall be the chief executive authority in the State for carrying into execution`
  line `the provisions of this Act and the rules and orders made thereunder subject to the directions, if any, given`
  line `by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chief Registrar shall take steps, by the issue of suitable instructions or otherwise, to`
  line `co-ordinate, unity and supervise the work of registration in the State for securing an efficient system of`
  line `registration and shall prepare and submit to the State Government, in such manner and at such intervals as`
  line `may be prescribed, a report on the working of this Act in the State along with the statistical report to in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 19.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (6759)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Registration divisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6759&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `divide the territory within the State into such registration divisions as it may think fit and prescribe`
  line `different rules for different registration divisions.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (6760)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `District Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6760&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may appoint a District Registrar for each revenue`
  line `district and such number of Additional District Registrars as it thinks fit who shall, subject to the general`
  line `control and direction of the District Registrar, discharge such functions of the District Registrar as the`
  line `District Registrar may, from time to time, authorise them to discharge.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Registrar shall superintend, subject to the direction of the Chief Registrar, the`
  line `registration of births and deaths in the district and shall be responsible for carrying into execution in the`
  line `district the provisions of this Act and the orders of the Chief Registrar issued from time to time for the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (6761)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Registrars.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6761&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may appoint a Registrar for each local area comprising the`
  line `area within the jurisdiction of a municipality, panchayat or other local authority or any other area or a`
  line `combination of any two or more of them:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may appoint in the case of a municipality, panchayat, or other`
  line `local authority, any officer or other employee thereof as a Registrar.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Registrar shall, without fee or reward, enter in the register maintained ^1[,electronically or`
  line `otherwise,] for the purpose all information given to him under section 8 or section 9 ^1[in respect of births`
  line `and deaths which has taken place in his jurisdiction] and shall also take steps to inform himself carefully`
  line `of every birth and of every death which takes place in his jurisdiction and to ascertain and register the`
  line `particulars required to be registered.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Registrar shall have an office in the local area for which he is appointed.`
  line
  line `(4) Every Registrar shall attend his office for the purpose of registering births and deaths on such days`
  line `and at such hours as the Chief Registrar may direct and shall cause to be placed in some conspicuous`
  line `place on or near the outer door of the office of the Registrar a board bearing, in the local language, his`
  line `name with the addition of Registrar of Births and Deaths for the local area for which he is appointed, and`
  line `the days and hours of his attendance.`
  line
  line `(5) The Registrar may, with the prior approval of the Chief Registrar, ^2[appoint Sub-Registrars and, in`
  line `the event of any disaster or epidemic, appoint Special Sub-Registrars] assign to them any or all of his`
  line `powers and duties in relation to specified areas within his jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the expressions, --`
  line
  line `(i) "disaster" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (d) of section 2 of the`
  line `Disaster Management Act, 2005 (53 of 2005);`
  line
  line `(ii) "epidemic" means the epidemic referred to in the Epidemic Diseases Act, 1897 (3 of 1897).]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2023, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "appoint sub-Registrars and" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (6762)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Persons required to register births and deaths.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6762&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the persons specified`
  line `below to give or cause to be given, either ^1[orally or in writing with signature], according to the best of`
  line `their knowledge and belief, within such time as may be prescribed, information to the Registrar of the`
  line `several particulars ^2[including the Aadhaar number of parents and the informant, if available, in case of`
  line `birth,] required to be entered in the forms prescribed by the State Government under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 16,--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of births and deaths in a house, whether residential or non-residential, not being any`
  line `place referred to in clauses (b) to (e) the head of the house or, in case more than one household live in`
  line `the house, the head of the household, the head being the person, who is so recognised by the house or`
  line `the household, and if he is not present in the house at any time during the period within which the`
  line `birth or death has to be reported, the nearest relative of the head present in the house, and in the`
  line `absence of any such person, the oldest adult ^3*** person present therein during the said period;`
  line
  line `^2[i(aa) in respect of non-institutional adoption, the adoptive parents;`
  line `(ab) in respect of birth of a child to a single parent or unwed mother from her womb, the parent;`
  line
  line `(ac) in respect of birth of a child through surrogacy, the biological parent;]`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of births and deaths in a hospital, health centre, maternity or nursing home or other`
  line `like institution, the medical officer in charge or any person authorised by him in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) in respect of births and deaths in a jail, the jailor in charge;`
  line
  line `(d) in respect of births and deaths in a choultry, chattram, hostel, dharmasala, boarding-house,`
  line `lodging-house, tavern, barrack, toddy shop or place of public resort, the person in charge thereof;`
  line
  line `^4[i(da) in respect of a child who is taken on adoption from the Specialised Adoption Agency, the`
  line `person in-charge of the Specialised Adoption Agency.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, the expression "Specialised Adoption Agency"`
  line `shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (57) of section 2 of the Juvenile Justice (Care`
  line `and Protection of Children) Act, 2015 (2 of 2016);`
  line
  line `(db) in respect of an orphan or abandoned child or surrendered child in any child care institution,`
  line `the person in-charge or caretaker of the child care institution.`
  line
  line `Explanation-For the purposes of this clause, the expressions "abandoned child" or "child care`
  line `institution" or "orphan" or "surrendered child" shall have the same meanings as respectively assigned`
  line `to them in clauses (1), (21), (42) and (60) of section 2 of the Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of`
  line `Children) Act, 2015 (2 of 2016);`
  line
  line `(dc) in respect of birth of a child through surrogacy in a surrogacy clinic, the person in-charge of`
  line `the surrogacy clinic.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, the expressions "surrogacy" and "surrogacy clinic"`
  line `shall have the same meanings as respectively assigned to them in clauses (zd) and (ze) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Surrogacy (Regulation) Act, 2021 (47 of 2021);]`
  line
  line `(e) in respect of any new-born child or dead body found deserted in a public place, the headman`
  line `or other corresponding officer of the village in the case of a village and the officer in charge of the`
  line `local police station elsewhere:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person who finds such child or dead body, or in whose charge such child or`
  line `dead body may be placed, shall notify such fact to the headman or officer aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(f) in any other place, such person as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the State Government, having regard to`
  line `the conditions obtaining in a registration division, may by order require that for such period as may be`
  line `specified in the order, any person specified by the State Government by designation in this behalf, shall`
  line `give or cause to be given information regarding births and deaths in a house referred to in clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) instead of the persons specified in that clause.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "orally or in writing" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. The word "male" omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2023, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (6763)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Special provisions regarding births and deaths in a plantation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6763&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `In the case of births and deaths`
  line `in a plantation, the superintendent of the plantation shall give or cause to be given to the Registrar the`
  line `information referred to in section 8:`
  line
  line `Provided that the persons referred to in clauses (a) to (f) of sub-section (1) of section 8 shall furnish`
  line `the necessary particulars to the superintendent of the plantation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression "plantation" means any land not less than four hectares`
  line `in extent which is being prepared for the production of, or actually produces, tea, coffee, pepper, rubber,`
  line `cardamom, cinchona or such other products as the State Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify and the expression "superintendent of the plantation" means the person having the charge`
  line `or supervision of the labourers and work in the plantation, whether called a manager, superintendent or by`
  line `any other name.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (6764)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Duty of certain persons to notify births and deaths and to certify cause of death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2023, s. 8, for sub-sections (2) and (3) (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6764&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall`
  line `be the duty of--`
  line
  line `(i) the midwife or any other medical or health attendant at a birth or death,`
  line
  line `(ii) the keeper or the owner of a place set apart for the disposal of dead bodies or any person`
  line `required by a local authority to be present at such place, or`
  line
  line `(iii) any other person whom the State Government may specify in this behalf by his designation,`
  line `to notify every birth or death or both at which he or she attended or was present, or which occurred in`
  line `such areas as may be prescribed, to the Registrar within such time and in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `^1[(2) Where death occurs in any medical institution providing specialised treatment or general`
  line `treatment, every such institution, irrespective of ownership, shall, free of charge, provide a certificate of`
  line `the cause of death, including the history of illness, if any, signed by the medical practitioner who attended`
  line `that person during his recent illness to the Registrar in such form as may be prescribed and provide a copy`
  line `of such certificate to the nearest relative.`
  line
  line `(3) In the event of death of any person occurring in any place other than medical institution, and such`
  line `person was, during his recent illness, attended to by a medical practitioner, such medical practitioner`
  line `shall, after the death of that person, free of charge, forthwith issue, a certificate of the cause of death,`
  line `including the history of illness, if any, to the person required under this Act to give information`
  line `concerning the death in such form as may be prescribed, and the person, on receipt of the certificate, shall`
  line `deliver the same to the Registrar at the time of giving information of the death as required under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (6765)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Informant to sign the register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "place of abode, and, if he cannot write" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6765&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Every person who has orally given to the Registrar any`
  line `information required under this Act shall write in the register maintained in this behalf, his name,`
  line `description and ^1[place of abode and put his signature thereto, and, if he cannot write], shall put his thumb`
  line `mark in the register against his name, description and place of abode, the particulars being in such a case`
  line `entered by the Registrar.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (6766)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Certificate of registration of births or deaths`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for section 12 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6766&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Certificate of registration of births or deaths.--The Registrar shall, as soon as the registration`
  line `of a birth or death has been completed, but not later than seven days, give, free of charge, electronically or`
  line `otherwise under his signature, to the person who gives information under section 8 or section 9, a`
  line `certificate extracted from the register relating to such birth or death in such form and manner as may be`
  line prescribed.]
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (6767)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Delayed registration of births and deaths.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for sub-sections (2) and (3) (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6767&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any birth or death of which information is`
  line `given to the Registrar after the expiry of the period specified therefor, but within thirty days of its`
  line `occurrence, shall be registered on payment of such late fee as may be prescribed.`
  line `^1[(2) Any birth or death of which delayed information is given to the Registrar after thirty days but`
  line `within one year of its occurrence, shall be registered only with the written permission of the District`
  line `Registrar or such other authority, on payment of such fee and on production of self-attested document in`
  line `such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any birth or death of which delayed information is given to the Registrar after one year of its`
  line `occurrence, shall be registered only on an order made by a District Magistrate or Sub-Divisional`
  line `Magistrate or by an Executive Magistrate authorised by the District Magistrate, having jurisdiction over`
  line `the area where the birth or death has taken place, after verifying the correctness of the birth or death and`
  line `on payment of such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "Executive Magistrate" means the`
  line `Executive Magistrate appointed under sub-section (1) of section 20 of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974).]`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this section shall be without prejudice to any action that may be taken against a`
  line `person for failure on his part to register any birth or death within the time specified therefor and any such`
  line `birth or death may be registered during the pendency of any such action.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (6768)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Registration of name of child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6768&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Where the birth of any child has been registered without a`
  line `name, the parent or guardian of such child shall within the prescribed period give information regarding`
  line `the name of the child to the Registrar either orally or in writing and thereupon the Registrar shall enter`
  line `such name in the register and initial and date the entry.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (6769)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Correction or cancellation of entry in the register of births and deaths.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6769&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `If it is proved to the`
  line `satisfaction of the Registrar that any entry of a birth or death in any register kept by him under this Act is`
  line `erroneous in form or substance, or has been fraudulently or improperly made, he may, subject to such`
  line `rules as may be made by the State Government with respect to the conditions on which and the`
  line `circumstances in which such entries may be corrected or cancelled, correct the error or cancel the entry`
  line `by suitable entry in the margin, without any alteration of the original entry, and shall sign the marginal`
  line `entry and add thereto the date of the correction or cancellation.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (6770)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Registrars to keep registers in the prescribed form.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2023, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6770&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Registrar shall keep in the`
  line `prescribed form a register of births and deaths ^1ic956electronically or otherwise,] for the registration area or`
  line `any part thereof in relation to which he exercises jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Registrar shall cause to be printed and supplied a sufficient number of register books`
  line `for making entries of births and deaths according to such forms and instructions as may, from time to`
  line `time, be prescribed; and a copy of such forms in the local language shall be posted in some conspicuous`
  line `place on or near the outer door of the office of every Registrar.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (6786)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Search of births and deaths register`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6786&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any rules made in this behalf by the State`
  line `Government, including rules relating to the payment of fees and postal charges, any person may--`
  line
  line `(a) cause a search to be made by the Registrar for any entry in a register of births and deaths; and`
  line
  line `^1[(b) obtain, electronically or otherwise, a certificate of birth or death from such register and`
  line `issued in such form and manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no certificate relating to any death, issued to any person, shall disclose the`
  line `particulars regarding the cause of death as entered in the register.]`
  line
  line `(2) All ^2[certificates] given under this section shall be certified by the Registrar or any other officer`
  line `authorised by the State Government to give such ^2[certificates] as provided in section 76 of the Indian`
  line `Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), and shall be admissible in evidence for the purpose of proving the birth`
  line `or death to which the entry relates.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the certificate`
  line `referred to in sub-section (2) or section 12, shall be used to prove the date and place of birth of a person`
  line `who is born on or after the date of commencement of the Registration of Births and Deaths (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 2023, for the purposes of--`
  line
  line `(a) admission to an educational institution;`
  line
  line `(b) issuance of a driving licence;`
  line
  line `(c) preparation of a voter list;`
  line
  line `(d) registration of a marriage;`
  line
  line `(e) appointment to a post in the Central Government or State Government or a local body or`
  line `public sector undertaking or in any statutory or autonomous body under the Central Government or`
  line `State Government;`
  line
  line `(f) issuance of a passport;`
  line
  line `(g) issuance of an Aadhaar number; and`
  line
  line `(h) any other purpose as may be determined by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for "extracts" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (6787)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Inspection of registration offices`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2023, s. 14, for "by the District Registrar" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6787&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The registration offices shall be inspected and the registers kept`
  line `therein shall be examined in such manner and by such authority as may be specified ^1[in general or special`
  line `order by the Chief Registrar".`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (6788)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Registrars to send periodical returns to the Chief Registrar for compilation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6788&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `Registrar shall send to the Chief Registrar or to any officer specified by him, at such intervals and in such`
  line `form as may be prescribed, a return regarding the entries of births and deaths in the register kept by such`
  line Registrar.
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Registrar shall cause the information in the returns furnished by the Registrars to be`
  line `compiled and shall publish for the information of the public a statistical report on the registered births and`
  line `deaths during the year at such intervals and in such form as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (6789)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Special provision as to registration of births and deaths of citizens outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Registrar-General" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6789&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `^1[Registrar General of India] shall, subject to such rules as may be made by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf, cause to be registered information as to births and deaths of citizens of India outside India received by`
  line `him under the rules relating to the registration of such citizens at Indian Consulates made under the Citizenship`
  line `Act, 1955 (57 of 1955), and every such registration shall also be deemed to have been duly made under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) In the case of any child born outside India in respect of whom information has not been received as`
  line `provided in sub-section (1), if the parents of the child return to India with a view to settling therein, they may,`
  line `at any time within sixty days from the date of the arrival of the child in India, get the birth of the child`
  line `registered under this Act in the same manner as if the child was born in India and the provisions of section 13`
  line `shall apply to the birth of such child after the expiry of the period of sixty days aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (6790)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power of Registrar to obtain information regarding birth or death`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6790&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar may either`
  line `orally or in writing require any person to furnish any information within his knowledge in connection`
  line `with a birth or death in the locality within which such person resides and that person shall be bound to`
  line `comply with such requisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (6791)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Powers to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6791&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such directions to any State`
  line `Government as may appear to be necessary for carrying into execution in the State any of the provisions`
  line `of this Act or of any rule or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (6792)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6792&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[Any person, except the person specified in sub-section (1A),] who--`
  line
  line `(a) fails without reasonable cause to give any information which it is his duty to give under any of the`
  line `provisions of sections 8 and 9; or`
  line
  line `(b) gives or causes to be given, for the purpose of being inserted in any register of births and deaths,`
  line `any information which he knows or believes to be false regarding any of the particulars required to be`
  line `known and registered; or`
  line
  line `(c) refuses to write his name, description and place of abode or to put his thumb mark ^2[or signature,`
  line `as the case may be,] in the register as required by section 11,`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to ^3[two hundred and fifty rupees].`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) Whoever, being a person specified in clauses (b), (c), (d), (da), (db), (dc) and (e) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 8, --`
  line
  line `(a) fails without reasonable cause to give any information which it is his duty to give; or`
  line
  line `(b) gives or causes to be given, for the purpose of being inserted in any register of births and`
  line `deaths, any information which he knows or believes to be false regarding any of the particulars`
  line `required to be known and registered; or`
  line
  line `(c) refuses to write his name, description and place of abode or to put his thumb mark or signature`
  line `in the register as required under section 11,`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees in respect of each birth or death.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any Registrar or Sub-Registrar who neglects or refuses, without reasonable cause, to register any`
  line `birth or death occurring in his jurisdiction ^4[or to give a certificate to the informant under section 12] or to`
  line `submit any returns as required by sub-section (1) of section 19 shall be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to ^5[two hundred and fifty rupees].`
  line
  line `^6[(3) Any person who neglects or refuses to provide or issue a certificate as required under`
  line `sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of section 10 or any person neglects or refuses to deliver such certificate`
  line `to the Registrar, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to fifty rupees.]`
  line
  line `(4) ^7[Any person except the person specified in sub-section (1A)] Any person who, without`
  line `reasonable cause, contravenes any provision of this Act for the contravention of which no penalty is`
  line `provided for in this section shall be punishable with fine which may extend to ^8[two hundred and fifty`
  line rupees].
  line
  line `^4[(4A) Any person specified in sub-section (1A), who, without reasonable cause, contravenes any`
  line `provision of this Act for the contravention of which no penalty is provided for in this section, shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees in respect of each birth or death.]`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in the ^9[Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1973)], an`
  line `offence under this section shall be tried summarily by a magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "Any person" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "fifty rupees" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2023, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "fifty rupees" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "Any Person" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "ten rupees" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (6793)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to compound offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6793&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, any officer`
  line `authorised by the Chief Registrar by a general or special order in this behalf may, either before or after the`
  line `institution of criminal ^1[proceedings under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) accept from the person, except the person specified in sub-section (1A) of section 23, who has`
  line `committed or is reasonably suspected of having committed an offence under this Act, by way of`
  line `composition of such offence a sum of money not exceeding two hundred and fifty rupees;`
  line
  line `(b) accept from the person specified in sub-section (1A) of section 23, who has committed or is`
  line `reasonably suspected of having committed an offence under this Act, by way of composition of such`
  line `offence a sum of money not exceeding one thousand rupees in respect of each birth or death.]`
  line
  line `(2) On the payment of such sum of money, such person shall be discharged and no further`
  line `proceedings shall be taken against him in respect of such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (6794)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Sanction for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6794&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for an offence punishable under this Act shall be`
  line `instituted except by an officer authorised by the Chief Registrar by general or special order in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25_a:
  sectionId (78054)
  sectionNo 25A
  orderNo 26
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 17, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=78054&sectionno=25A&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[25A. Appeal.--(1) Any person aggrieved by any action or order of,--`
  line
  line `(i) the Registrar, may prefer an appeal to the District Registrar; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the District Registrar, may prefer an appeal to the Chief Registrar,`
  line
  line `within a period of thirty days from the date of such action or receipt of such order, as the case`
  line `may be, in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Registrar or the Chief Registrar, as the case may be, shall decide the appeal referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1) within a period of ninety days from the date of preferring of such appeal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (6795)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Registrars and Sub-Registrars to be deemed public servants`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6795&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `All Registrars and`
  line `Sub-Registrars shall, while acting or purporting to act in pursuance of the provisions of this Act or any`
  line `rule or order made thereunder, be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (6796)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6796&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act (except the power to make rules under section 30) or`
  line `the rules made thereunder shall, subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the direction, be`
  line `exercisable, also by such officer or authority subordinate to the State Government as may be specified in`
  line `the direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (6797)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2023, s. 2, for "Registrar-General" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6797&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Government, the ^1[Registrar General of India], any Registrar, or any person exercising`
  line `any power or performing any duty under this Act for anything which is in good faith done or intended to`
  line `be done in pursuance of this Act or any rule or order made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Government for any damage caused or likely`
  line `to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance, of this Act or`
  line `any rule or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (6798)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Act not to be in derogation of Act 6 of 1886`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6798&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall be construed to be in`
  line `derogation of the provisions of the Births, Deaths and Marriages Registration Act, 1886.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (6799)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6799&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, with the approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the forms of registers of births and deaths required to be kept under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the period within which and the form and the manner in which information should be given to`
  line `the registrar under section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) the period within which and the manner in which births and deaths shall be notified under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `^1[(d) the form of certificate of the cause of death under sub-section (2) and (3) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) the particulars of which extract may be given under section 12;`
  line
  line `(f) the authority which may grant permission for registration of a birth or death under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 13;]`
  line
  line `(g) the fees payable for registration made under section 13;`
  line
  line `^2[(ga) the form and manner in which the certificate of birth or death may be obtained under`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(gb) the form and manner of preferring an appeal under sub-section (1) of section 25A;]`
  line `(h) the submission of reports by the Chief Registrar under sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(i) the search of birth and death registers and the fees payable for such search and for the`
  line `grant of ^3[certificates] from the registers;`
  line
  line `(j) the forms in which and the intervals at which the returns and the statistical report under`
  line `section 19 shall be furnished and published;`
  line
  line `(k) the custody, production and transfer of the registers and other records kept by Registrars;`
  line
  line `(l) the correction of errors and the cancellation of entries in the register of births and deaths;`
  line
  line `(m) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before the State`
  line Legislature.]
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for clauses (d), (e) and (f) (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for "extracts" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (6800)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6800&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 29, as from the coming into force of`
  line `this Act in any State or part thereof, so much of any law in force therein as relates to the matters covered`
  line `by this Act shall stand repealed in such State or part, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken (including any instruction or`
  line `direction issued, any regulation or rule or order made) under any such law shall, in so far as such thing or`
  line `action is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done or taken under the`
  line `provisions aforesaid, as if they were in force when such thing was done or such action was taken, and`
  line `shall continue in force accordingly until superseded by anything done or any action taken under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (6801)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power to remove difficulty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141&sectionId=6801&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00006_196918_1517807324141
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect in a State to the provisions`
  line `of this Act in their application to any area, the State Government may, with the approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by order make such provisions or give such directions not inconsistent with the provisions`
  line `of this Act as appears to the State Government to be necessary or expedient for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section in relation to any area in a State after the`
  line `expiration of two years from the date on which this Act comes into force in that area.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
  title `जन्‍म और मृत्‍यु रजिस्‍ट्रीकरण अधिनियम, 1969`
